    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burlingame</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 55.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 26th of November
                            last, No. 59, has been received. I have learned with much satisfaction
                            of the friendly dispositions manifested towards the United States by
                            your diplomatic colleagues at Peking. Your letter to Sir Frederick
                            Bruce, in acknowledgment of the course pursued by him in regard to the
                            Osborne flotilla, is approved and commended; and I shall request Mr.
                            Adams to make a further expression at London of the estimation in which
                            Sir Frederick’s conduct is held by this government.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD,</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
